# LXR Mailbox — resource identity (treat as product / license integrity)

These rules override convenience, “cleanup,” or “readability” refactors. Violating them is unacceptable.

## Canonical deploy name

- The resource folder **must** be **`lxr-mailbox`**. Same for `exports['lxr-mailbox']`, events, and support docs.

## Where enforcement lives (only here)

- **No** separate integrity-only script (e.g. no `resource_integrity.lua` / `resource_guard.lua`).
- Identity check is **only** in **`client/client.lua`** and **`server/server.lua`**, **immediately after** the closing `]]` of the mandatory LXR ASCII banner (see `lxr-ascii-banners.mdc` — never strip or move the banner to “save lines”).
- Do **not** put a redundant plain-text `REQUIRED = 'lxr-mailbox'` block in **`config.lua`**, **`shared/*`**, or other open-edited files so casual buyers get a rename recipe next to settings.

## fxmanifest load order (mandatory)

- **`client/client.lua`** must be the **first** entry in `client_scripts`.
- **`server/server.lua`** must be the **first** entry in `server_scripts` (before `@oxmysql/lib/MySQL.lua` and every other server file).

## Behaviour

- On wrong `GetCurrentResourceName()`, both entrypoints **`error('...', 0)`** at load time — **hard stop**. No downgrading to `print`, Notify, or “soft” warnings.

## Tebex / escrow intent

- **`client/client.lua`** and **`server/server.lua`** are the **intended Tebex escrow assets** for identity logic. Do not relocate the fatal check solely into non-escrow, buyer-editable files.

## Implementation discipline

- Do not replace **`string.char`-based** (or equivalent non-obvious) expected-name construction with a **bare `'lxr-mailbox'` literal** in those two files just to “make grep easier” for developers — that defeats the anti–trivial-tamper goal unless the owner explicitly asks.
- When touching those two files, **preserve** the identity `do ... end` block verbatim unless fixing a real bug.

## AI / refactors

- Never suggest renaming the resource, removing the first-slot entries from the manifest, or “moving config-only” checks as the sole guard.
- If asked to “remove duplication,” the answer is **no** — duplication across **only** these two escrow-style entrypoints is intentional; duplication into `config.lua` is **not** allowed.
